      "type": "edit",
      "id": "5131371f8bcf7420",
      "item": {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "id": "5131371f8bcf7420",
        "text": "Such ghost speech, which was only understood by those who believed they could continue to hope for revolution, soon had to become the central problem of critical theory itself, challenging metaphysics. It turned out that anti-Semitism, unlike any other prejudice, even a racist one, raises the question of totality in nuce by answering it with annihilation - the question of how the unity of society is established in consciousness as well as in politics. This shows the weakness of the concept of state capitalism with which Horkheimer, following Friedrich Pollock, tries to grasp the totalitarian order and according to which it is in principle possible for the state, whether in the New Deal of Roosevelt's USA or in the economic miracle of Hitler's Third Reich, to eliminate the sphere of circulation. As if it could be completely annulled in Germany without at the same time, as Karl Kraus already knew, reducing \"the life of the state, of the economy, of the cultural exercise to the simplest formula\": \"that of annihilation \"8 - not of the rule of man over man, whose formula has become the law of value, but of annihilation aimed at the \"total enemy\". To this formula, which the concept of state capitalism did not know, then also belongs that in the process whoever stands in the way or puts himself in the way can still be included in varying degrees as an aspect of that total enemy at any time."
