      "id": "ffbc0dd725adb729",
      "item": {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "id": "ffbc0dd725adb729",
        "text": "Just as Neumann, for example, denied a \"primacy of politics\" which the talk of state capitalism asserted and which should actually be called \"primacy of domestic politics\"; just as he wanted to prove that the state, even in this crisis in Germany, had absolutely no possibilities to simply abolish class rule and market mechanism domestically through planning, he himself came to quite different results than refutation and proof actually required. That the \"primacy of politics\" over economics was thus by no means established and could never be established within the boundaries of the nation-state, he tried to prove by means of empirical studies of the German economy and fundamentally doubted the stability of the Nazi system, convinced that the capitalist contradictions in Germany had to have an effect on a 'higher' level, even if they were concealed by a bureaucratic apparatus and Volksgemeinschafts propaganda; on a higher level meant: that they made war and ruthless expansion inevitable.19"
